<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9264> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9264" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Senator. A juror in 74 in the trial of Oppianicus, whose father[84x] disinherited him for accepting bribes (Cic. Cluent. 135, Egnatius). The description of the father as Cn. Egnatius pater indicates that both had the same praenomen, and the son should be distinguished from the monetalis (see below, no. 27). See Syme, Historia 4, 1955, 61?RP 1.280-281; Shackleton Bailey, Studies 36." .
